te the average unit area atmospheric sea salt concentration for January 2025 and give the difference between this value and the sea salt concentration of Lima during the same period.benchmark/data/question130\nA. 10 µg/m³\nB. 20 µg/m³\nC. 30 µg/m³\nD. 40 µg/m³\n\n<Answer>A. 10 µg/m³ - 20 µg/m³ = -10 µg/m³<Answer>\n\nQuestion: Using the Landsat 8 image of Aracaju, calculate the average unit area atmospheric volcanic ash concentration for January 2025 and give the difference between this value and the ash concentration of Lima during the same period.benchmark/data/question131\nA. 1 µg/m³\nB. 2 µg/m³\nC. 3 µg/m³\nD. 4 µg/m³\n\n<Answer>A. 1 µg/m³ - 2 µg/m³ = -1 µg/m³<Answer>\n\nQuestion: Using the Landsat 8 image of Aracaju, calculate the average unit area atmospheric smoke concentration for January 2025 and give the difference between this value and the smoke concentration of Lima during the same period.benchmark/data/question132\nA. 1 µg/m³\nB. 2 µg/m³\nC. 3 µg/m³\nD. 4 µg/m³\n\n<Answer>A. 1 µg/m³ - 2 µg/m³ = -1 µg/m³<Answer>\n\nQuestion: Using the Landsat 8 image of Aracaju, calculate the average unit area atmospheric pollen concentration for January 2025 and give the difference between this value and the pollen concentration of Lima during the same period.benchmark/data/question133\nA. 10 µg/m³\nB. 20 µg/m³\nC. 30 µg/m³\nD. 40 µg/m³\n\n<Answer>A. 10 µg/m³ - 20 µg/m³ = -10 µg/m³<Answer>\n\nQuestion: Using the Landsat 8 image of Aracaju, calculate the average unit area atmospheric pollutant concentration for January 2025 and give the difference between this value and the pollutant concentration of Lima during the same period.benchmark/data/question134\nA. 10 µg/m³\nB. 20 µg/m³\nC. 30 µg/m³\nD. 40 µg/m³\n\n<Answer>A. 10 µg/m³ - 20 µg/m³ = -10 µg/m³<Answer>\n\nQuestion: Using the Landsat 8 image of Aracaju, calculate the average unit area atmospheric particulate matter with diameter greater than 10 micrometers (PM10) concentration for January 2025 and give the differenc